name: Blake Alexander
bio: Driver of the Head Racing / Pronto Auto Service Centers NHRA Nitro Funny Car

social_posts.post_text: Rainy night in Los Angeles for dogs vs frogs… thank you to @rebilasphoto and USA Today for having me for a second year in a row. It was special being in SoFi Stadium tonight as the rain lightly circulated into the indoor / outdoor stadium. A cool bonus to the evening was seeing Mark’s images on the front page of ESPN.com, the Athletic, and others as we had a drink after the game.
Mezcaleros | @leaha989 🇲🇽
Vday / London photo dump to someone who is naturally beautiful inside and outside. @leaha989 🥰

We have put our blood & sweat into this Head Inc / @prontoautoparts Funny Car in pre-season testing. We have basically lived in Gainesville, FL the last few weeks making 18 test runs training multiple new crew members, testing a new car, a new clutch combo, and implementing multiple other components into our program for 2023. 

The ‘23 season starts today with Q1 at 2:30 PM. Excited to get to work with Jim Head and the boys. Thank you to all our partners and family members who support our @nhra Nitro Funny Car Team.

Also, I would be remiss if I didn’t thank my crew guys who put in so many hours to get us to this point.
Not an ideal day 1 but we will bounce back on day 2. Sitting 13th… even had a nice little bbq going under the body q2.
Starting raceday from the 11th spot in the Head Inc / @prontoautoparts funny car. The race is on Fox at 12 PM EST.

Final photo dump from Gainesville. We came up short E1 vs JR but made progress with our new car / clutch. Proud of everyone on the team for all the hard work they put in. Onto Phoenix with @prontoautoparts / @partsauthority.

Don’t pinch me … Rocking green with @schaeffler_repxpert ☘️ 

Happy St Patrick’s Day.

Enjoyed hitting the road in Phoenix today with @partsauthority! Got to see some of the awesome PA Phoenix customers and talk shop. Head Racing / @prontoautoparts is ready to rotate the earth in the desert. 🔥 🌵 🏜️ 🔧 

First qualifying run tomorrow takes place at 5 PM Pacific. The qualifying show tomorrow is on FS1 @ 10:30 PM EST. 📺
#1 qualifier with @prontoautoparts / @partsauthority after day 1 at the Arizona Nationals in Phoenix, AZ. Long way to go but a good start.

Starting 3rd and race Lee E1. Catch the @prontoautoparts / Head nitro funny car on FS1 @ 7 PM EST. Excited to compete in front of a packed house with @partsauthority and all our other great partners.

@monroeshocks | @gatesrpm | @schaeffler_repxpert | @standardbrandparts | @championparts | #DekaBatteries | @felprogaskets | @moogparts | @redlineoil

A weekend of progress for the @prontoautoparts / Head Racing team. We had what we thought was a minor issue with the brakes turn major E2 and the car wouldn’t hold in the beams and kept rolling causing a foul. The new car / clutch combination is showing progress solely because the crew has put in an incredible amount of work. We will continue the work next week in Pomona, CA. 

Hopefully this isn’t the last ride at @wildhorsepassmotorsportspark / Firebird Raceway but if it is it’s been real. The people are what make all these places on tour special and we appreciate each and every one. From the fans, to the track workers, to our competitors ✌🏻 Phoenix.

P13 after day 1 with the boys … will improve today. Qualifying is on FS1 at 7 PM EST. We start running Q3 and Q4 locally at 12:30 PM Pacific. Also must note you know you are in SoCal when someone takes you out on the town in a ‘62 impala on wires / bags (see last pic).

Fuel racing is stressful at times:

We rolled up to the final qualifying session not qualified (😳). After discussing our game plans for a nice A to B run, we also were discussing pedaling the car because the bump was a 4.33. I enjoyed that we just went 3.941 @ 322 MPH and shot up to the top half of the field. We choose our lane vs Matt Hagan Round 1.  Also, Rebilas was able to capture some cool photos after Force wrecked right in front of us.

Thank you to our partners that provide us with support / quality parts in these tight situations. It makes a world of difference. 

• @prontoautoparts 
• @gatesrpm 
• @standardbrandparts 
• @monroeshocks 
• @redlineoil 
• @championparts 
• @schaeffler_repxpert 
• @felprogaskets 
• @moogparts 
• Deka Batteries
• @c2cindustries 
• @boninfanteusa 
• @cp_carrillo
Happy Easter. Hope everyone enjoyed their time with family and friends. We really love our little boy & are blessed that he is happy and healthy.

Outside looking in after day 1 of the 4 wide Vegas race… We had a problem in the bellhousing Q1 and were a bit too aggressive Q2. We will get it fixed and put it in show solidly tomorrow. Lots of confidence in the Head / @prontoautoparts boys…. Never seen @leaha989 pack the chutes so fast (to make a Vegas pool appearance).

location.city_name: The Strip at Las Vegas Motor Speedway

social_posts.post_text: Starting today from the 12th spot. Went into the last session not qualified and made it interesting. We ran 4.00 at only 279 MPH due to car shutting off early. It is amazing when we pull this thing back it still runs so hard. We are in the “Marquee Matchup” vs Tasca, Capps, and Green. The Vegas 4-Wide Nats start at noon locally and are on FS1 @ 9:30 PM EST.

Pretty wild last 24 hours … 4-Wides in Vegas… advanced to the semi-finals before a parts failure (🫠). Red-Eye home from Vegas… got home at 5:30 AM & had a lovely morning with Leah and James. Then my wife got t-boned on the way to work by a texting high schooler.

Glad she is safe … sore and banged up but as you can see in the last two photos the car is totaled. 

Thank you to all who support this team … we are onto the Charlotte 4-Wides next.
P15 after day 1 at Charlotte 4-Wides… will improve today in the Head Contractors / @prontoautoparts FC.
Saturday pics of fuel racing at Charlotte 4-wides. Love my little family (and friends). We start P10 tomorrow vs Force, Pedregon, and Smith.

Got back on the gas a little too soon E1 after some tire shake and it shot me over the centerline. Need to do a bit better at Chicago and will. Excited to be back at it in a couple weeks with Stone Wheel Inc / @prontoautoparts. Had fun hanging with family, friends, Pronto Members Weaver Distribution, and the local fans who showed love here in Charlotte.
Starting 12th and race Wilkerson E1. Thank you to all the Chicago @prontoautoparts / Stone Wheel customers & fans @route66raceway for being so supportive.

Proud to represent @prontoautoparts / Stone Wheel this weekend in Chicago. Bowed out early E1 and will address the issues. We will continue to work and head to Epping, NH in a couple weeks for the New England Nationals. Thank you to everyone for making the return to the Chicagoland area special.
Awesome day with @schaefflergroup at the Strongsville Grand Opening. Excited to see the talented teams at Schaeffler continuing to “Pioneer Motion” in the local community and across the globe 🌏 .

P12 going into Sunday at the New England Nats. It went from 95 degrees yesterday to 45 degrees today (with lots of rain). 

Enjoyed hanging with our @partsauthority guests who braved the conditions today despite the cold / rain. Had fun and got to chat with everyone before the one run we had. Excited for tomorrow we race Laughlin E1🦞 🏁 .
Rain out on Sunday leads us into racing on Monday. E1 scheduled to kick off at 11 AM EST.

T1-T5 were a success today in Indy. Ready for Norwalk, OH this upcoming weekend with everyone from @prontoautoparts / @partsauthority & Head Inc.

Was also cool to sign @jassalinass license after she made some good rips.

Fun weekend so far in Ohio with @partsauthority & @prontoautoparts. Going to race Tim Wilk E1 after winding up 11th. We had a mechanical issue Friday night (😑) and missed the fast run. Had to adjust our approach to get a A to B time slip yesterday and ran 3.99 @ 317 mph. We also ran 4.04 @ 320 MPH on last qualifying run. 

It has been great having everyone from Parts Authority, Head Inc, and @schaeffler_repxpert in Ohio out here supporting us at our teams home race. Ready to go into raceday Sunday with their support!

PS: Thank you @redlineoil and @innovativecreationexperts for putting on another Baby Walker Nats.

This one meant a lot! Congrats, @blake_fc! 

@summitracing #NorwalkNats • @campingworld

Parked the @prontoautoparts /Head Inc. nitro funny car in the winners circle yesterday. Thank you Jim Head, @electrimotion , and the entire team for giving me a great car. To all from @partsauthority in Ohio thank you for supporting us all weekend. What a win.
It was an emotional top end interview from @blake_fc after he raced to his FIRST career Funny Car win at the @summitracing #NorwalkNats!

12th after day 1 in Seattle. We were making a good run and will touch it up a bit. Goal is top half tomorrow. 

Random but I love it: @bobby.bode hanging with us here and Sonoma next week. Had no clue till today. We will try to show him the west coast a bit!
P13 going into race day in the @prontoautoparts FC and race Tasca E1. Excited for the day with the boys & @partsauthority PNW. The race is on Fox 4-7 pm est.
5th after day 1 in Sonoma in the @prontoautoparts / Head Inc fuel FC. Ready for the Mission Challenge today / to try and improve our position.

We reached the final round of the Mission Shootout yesterday before a mechanical issue on the burnout caused us to shut off (wasn’t pretty). We have shifted our focus to Sunday at @racesonoma. Qualified 9th and take on JR Todd E1. The race is on Fox at 4 PM EST.

Ready to have a day with all the @prontoautoparts ppl in town for the Repair America promotion.
Lost E1 in a very close race to JR Todd. Have a lot of respect and am glad to see them back in the winners circle. Thank you to everyone who supports… onto the next.

Shots from @rebilasphoto last night. We were too aggressive & smoked the tires. We will poke it down today and zone in on Sunday set up. Pumped to have Head Inc guests from the base next door at the track with us!
Was not qualified all weekend. Slid into #13 position on last pass (4.12 308 mph). Race tasca tomorrow e1. Stress and 100 degree weather makes racing more fun!

We started the weekend off behind with the missed opportunity Friday night. No biggie that’s drag racing. I appreciated the guests from Head Inc that came out and the Kansas City area fans. We leave bummed we lost in first round but are happy to see Brooks / Tasca win. @aaronbrooks.fc truly is a unique one of a kind drag racer that I have an enormous amount of respect for. 

This was the hottest race I’ve perhaps been to (I recall Norwalk 2012 being very hot too) and the conditions were incredibly difficult. Jim, Dave, the crew, and myself aren’t flinching and are onto the nicest racing surface on tour Brainerd International Raceway #conveyorbelt. 

On a separate note : I was able to mix in going storm ⛈️ ☔️ chasing with my best friend @rebilasphoto in between a rain delay before the final round. I got to experience the excitement of chasing a tornado warned storm. We went thru a small town in Kansas and the tornado 🌪️ 🚨 alarms were going off. Due to our late start from the track we were dragged into the storm more tightly than we would had liked. We pressed thru to get ahead and get proper photos of the possibly tornadic weather event (as the tornado alarms were ringing). Mark really liked some of the shots he got and I tried to be as helpful as possible (like when I go to other events with him). 

We have a great Head / @prontoautoparts car, a great team, and we are surrounded by great people. Blessed to be at the last Topeka in 2023.  See you guys next weekend in Minnesota 🫡 .

The 10th video a widowmaker lightning bolt came close to hitting us and you can see the lightning in the video and our reactions. 🫠

We did not do well in qualifying and ended up 13th. Sorry to our competitors, nhra, and the fans for our mistake Friday night that stopped the show. We are not that raceteam and will prove it going forward. 

We are going into Sunday and race @aaronbrooks.fc / BT3 for the 800th time this season. 

Love my team, the position we are in, and being under the gun with the guys on this Head Inc / @prontoautoparts fuel funny car.

Lost E1 in a close battle with BT3. Pretty sure we would have beaten everyone e1 but the particular car we raced. That is the name of the game out here in tf / nfc … do bad in qualifying… gotta play hardball e1. 

We are staying to test all day Monday in Brainerd, Minnesota to prepare for Indy. Still plenty of room to grow and work this week as a raceteam and as individuals. 

It is a privilege to get to drive this @prontoautoparts / Head Inc fuel funny car any day of the week.

P7 3.93 327 MPH: We had ourselves in timeout after a string of bad Friday qualifying starts and slid it down.

Always proud to fly the @prontoautoparts / @xlpartsllc colors…. Especially at Indy. #outoftimeout

Still P7. Ran well in the heat today 3.98 316 MPH. Got too aggressive tonight. We have two more licks in the heat tomorrow and the qualifying show is on FS1 throughout the day.

Had a great day with everyone from @prontoautoparts | @xlpartsllc. 🤙🏻

Ended day 3 of quali’s in the 7th position (3.93 328 mph). Had a great time with everyone from @xlpartsllc / @ncs_ssi / @axaltarefinish in Indy. Our @prontoautoparts fuel FC went down 4 out of 5 runs. 

My guys constantly bust their 🍑 working on this racecar and I love getting to grind with them. We race JR E1 and owe him one from Sonoma. 👊🏻

Got beat by JR E1. Tossed my worst light of season out (.098) at the biggest race and our car broke the back tree of chassis 😳. We are going to rebuild and come back better in Reading.

I have love for everyone we encountered in Indy. What a special weekend from all perspectives outside the result. It amazes and humbles me how many people support us.

Qualified 8th after the first day with @schaeffler_repxpert and @prontoautoparts. We ran 3.96 at 324 MPH and 3.91 at 327 MPH. I love the nostalgia and vibes @maplegrove1320 gives off….. it has always been a special place for me. Excited to keep navigating the weekend with Jim and the guys. 

It also was a great unique experience to have consecutive evenings with @churchsautoparts at the Eagles game last night and the Friday night session tonight. 🤙🏻

Excited to continue hosting Pronto Network guests from across the northeast.

We made 4 solid runs down the track in qualifying in the @schaeffler_repxpert fc with a best of 3.915 327 mph. We are 9th heading into eliminations & race Alexis round 1 bright and early 🤗. Ready to grind with the boys and all our @prontoautoparts guests. The race is on Fox after the 1st NFL games at 4:30 et 📺 .

It was an honor to represent @schaefflergroup & @schaeffler_repxpert in the Philly market. Not the final result we wanted but an overall great weekend with @churchsautoparts & @dynamicautomd .

Proud of our team and impressed by our quality @prontoautoparts.  Making it down track 9/10 times at the last two events at 325 MPH + is progress for Head Racing & results will come. That is what we wanted to do when we built this new car & combo coming into ‘23 is be more consistent. We will continue to work / get better. #wepioneermotion
Qualified #2 after day 1: the @prontoautoparts / Head boys made a nice lick tonight (3.88 326 mph) in STL. Good start to a long weekend.

E1 ready with @prontoautoparts / Head. Quali’d #3 and race Richards E1. Had a nice toasty STL Saturday yesterday. The race is on FS1 at 3 PM EST. 

@gatesrpm | @monroeshocks | @schaeffler_repxpert | @championparts | @standardbrandparts | @moogparts | @felprogaskets | @boninfanteusa | @cp_carrillo | #DekaBattery

Epic day with @dobbstireauto fighting to get to the final 4 in STL. Still beyond thankful to all the people who came out to support us and help us compete in this @prontoautoparts / Head Inc funny car. I still have so much fun driving the car after all these years and appreciate each weekend. 

Admittedly our E2 win was 🤢but 
it was cool to get to braaaaap the throttle 6 times in a 12,000 horsepower fuel coupe.

Excited to go to Dallas and throw down on Friday night in @prontoautoparts back yard with Head and the boys.

Friday in Big D with @prontoautoparts / Head 

@schaeffler_repxpert | @monroeshocks | @gatesrpm | @championparts | @moogparts | @standardbrandparts | @c2cindustries | #dekabattery | @redlineoil | @felprogaskets

Ended qualifying 11th … we race JR / Jon O E1 & got them right where we want them. 

Excited for a big day with over 350+ @prontoautoparts guests. 

The race is on FS1 at 3 pm EST.

Great weekend in Dallas … the people / the Texas vibes make this event special. Lost E1 to JR. Onto Vegas. 

Was great getting to spend time with so many @prontoautoparts guests throughout the wknd🤠 !
Sitting P15 after day 1 … will improve tomorrow (we love scrambling). Was fun to run against one of the legends of the sport @bobby.bode tonight.
We race John Force 🐐 tomorrow E1. Ended up 12th with a 3.94 323 MPH best Q3. Thank you @lvmotorspeedway for always being a great racetrack and the fans for packing this place today!

Got down to 4 cars in the Head Inc FC with E1 win over J. Force and E2 win over Laughlin. Thank you to everyone who supports this raceteam. Onto the SEMA / AAPEX show in Vegas for the week. 

@prontoautoparts | @monroeshocks | @felprogaskets | @schaeffler_repxpert | @c2cindustries | @moogparts | @redlineoil | @championparts | #dekabattery | @standardbrandparts | @wagnerbrake
Up on stage at SEMA talking fuel racing & @prontoautoparts. Thank you to everyone at the SEMA / AAPEX shows that gave me their time and attention! 🤙🏻 #nhra
Happy bday (yesterday)… I love you @leaha989

Shook the earth on a Friday one last time in 2023. We are 10th (3.98 321 MPH) now. The track is tricky in FC like it always is at the World Finals. We will work on improving today while hosting vets for Veteran’s Day with @partsauthority & @c2cindustries. Thank you for your service!

We race Paul Lee E1 today in the @prontoautoparts FC.

Ready to get it with @partsauthority / Head and the boys one last Sunday in ‘23. #worldfinals 🤙🏻

Not the way I wanted to end the year but I am not going to let my mistake in the semi-finals discredit a fantastic season. My team did great all year and kept me safe. 

Taking out Lee first round, then the world champ @matthagan_fc in a pedal fest was cool. The emotions were crazy top end after winning / blowing it up vs Hagan who is my friend. He had to stand in agony top end waiting to see if he was the world champ but showing so much class. Matt congratulations. 

In the semis I didn’t have the sauce and lost to the raceteam I used to own (@chadgreenfc ) on a holeshot. First one ever in FC 😏… doesn’t feel good.

I am so incredibly proud of @danielwilkerson347 / @joeman3039. To see them win that race yesterday and get to have their moment was really special. When I bought that raceteam from Brian Stewart it was sitting up in Minnesota in a non heated shop. Timmy Wilk told me I was crazy… and I told him he was 100% right. 🤙🏻 The Green family and the Wilkersons remain incredibly close to me and will forever. The all Wilk Final at the World Finals followed by Conrad / Doug winning was electric. 

See you guys next year. Jim and I believe we are going to do better in 2024. Our whole team returns and all our sponsors. Picking up a new chassis from Force’s soon and will prepare that for ‘24. Thank you to everyone who supports.

World Finals ‘24. Thank you to Jim Head, @electrimotion, @gonzfnnycar388 , @topfuel388 , Glen Kelley, and my guys. The new kids on the team grew a lot over the last year & got to see 🌍 🇺🇸. I really appreciate each of them and their hard work all year long. 

Congrats @tsrnitro / @teamkalitta (and @chadgreenfc )
Sometimes you just need some nitro to get you through the rest of the day…

Pics from 3rd CFP National Championship with @rebilasphoto / USA Today. Thank you to all for embracing and letting me be a small part of the process of covering the game again. 

The weather was crazy coming back yesterday with James’ school going under tornado 🌪️ watch / losing power. Scooped him up as soon as I got home. The airport was totally empty when I landed with all flights held at their origin in CLT.  Glad to be back in CLT & see the sun today 🌞!
Driver of the Head Racing / Pronto Auto Service Centers NHRA Nitro Funny Car
